  "bib_entries": {
    "15693740": {
      "title": "The quasi-Weierstra\u00df form for regular matrix pencils",
      "abstract": "Regular linear matrix pencils A \u2212 E\u2202 \u2208 K n\u00d7n (\u2202), where K = Q, R or C, and the associated differential algebraic equation (DAE) E u x = Ax are studied. The Wong sequences of subspaces are investigate and invoked to decompose the K n into V \ufffd \u2295 W \ufffd , where any bases of the linear spaces V \ufffd and Wtransform the matrix pencil into the Quasi-Weierstras form. The Quasi-Weierstras form of the matrix pencil decouples the original DAE into the underlying ODE and the pure DAE or, in other words, decouples the set of initial values into the set of consistent initial values Vand \"pure\" inconsistent initial values W \ufffd \\ {0}. Furthermore, Vand Ware spanned by the general- ized eigenvectors at the finite and infinite eigenvalues, resp. The Quasi-Weierstras form is used to show how chains of generalized eigenvectors at finite and infinite eigenvalues of A \u2212 E\u2202 lead to the well-known Weierstras form. So the latter can be viewed as a generalized Jordan form. Finally, it is shown how eigenvector chains constitute a basis for the solution space of E u x = Ax."
    }
  }
}